<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">My suggestion would be to wear some sort of banded mail, or plate mail.  Of course I'm joking, since that is not available to wizards.  So, what I really mean is that you might start grouping with classes that CAN wear that armor type.  Since you do not have your own "pet," try looking for an interactive one.  Sure, you might still get the mobs to jump you, but if you stay back, there is a good chance that with another character standing by the mob, it will leave you alone a little longer, and beat up on your buddy.<p>

Suggestion, cast some lower level spells during the fight, and use your most destructive spell when the mob is at it's weakest.  Learn how much damage your spell will do.  If it doesn't kill it outright, it might be enough to make it run.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
