<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Your discription sounds about right.<p>

As a wizard, i have never been able to solo white cons. Just cant do it.<p>

Blue cons i have a chance against, but even then, im going to get killed sooner or later. Just one fatal mistake (or resist).<p>

If something cons blue/ almost green.... or better yet ... green but i still get exp for it... i can solo it safely. Its just the nature of the wizard. Its why so many people complain that wizards are too weak compared to other classes, i would assume.<p>

One exception, I was able to kill blue con evil eyes with little difficulty. Wizards are better suited to killing enchanter/wizard classes, because a wizard can actually deal enough damage to make the kill before they are out of mana.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
